    "body": "Automatically checks if the current code is up- to- date and updates the cache.\n\n#### Verification environment\n-  Nuxt: 2.15.8\n-  @nuxtjs/pwa: 3.3.5\n\n#### Code\n`nuxt.config.js`.\n\n```js\n{\n  plugins: ['plugins/prompt-update.js']\n}\n```\n\n`plugins/prompt- update.js`.\n\n```js\nexport default async () => {\n  if ('serviceWorker' in navigator) {\n    navigator.serviceWorker.getRegistration(\"/sw.js\").then(registration => {\n      setInterval(()=>{registration.update()}, 1000)\n      registration.onupdatefound  = () => window.location.reload()\n    })\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `1000` part of `setInterval` is an arbitrary span to check for updates (in milliseconds).\nWith `registration.update()`, a request is sent to `/sw.js` to detect that the internal `revision` value has changed and reload the file.\n\n#### Methods of operation check\nYou can confirm that it is automatically updated by distributing it with `npm run generate`, `http- server dist/ - p 3000` and then generate it again after changing the internal files.\n\nThe following network log confirms that `sw.js` is checked for updates.\n```\n[2022-02-05T11:06:44.398Z]  \"GET /sw.js\" \"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) ...\"\n```",
